12 0 obj
<< /Length 1670 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Intermittent Fasting) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (How IF Works) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (When you fast, several things happen in your body:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (- Insulin levels drop significantly \(promotes fat burning\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Human Growth Hormone increases \(muscle preservation\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (- Cellular repair processes activate \(autophagy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Gene expression changes \(longevity and protection genes\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 570.4 Td (Benefits of Intermittent Fasting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.4 Td (- Weight and body fat loss \(especially visceral fat\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- Improved insulin sensitivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- Reduced inflammation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Better brain function and clarity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 496.4 Td (- Cellular cleanup \(autophagy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 482.4 Td (- Simplified eating schedule) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 468.4 Td (- May improve cholesterol and blood pressure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 454.4 Td (- Potential longevity benefits) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 424.6 Td (Who Should NOT Fast) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.6 Td (- Pregnant or breastfeeding women) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 392.6 Td (- Children and teenagers) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 378.6 Td (- People with eating disorder history) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 364.6 Td (- Those with Type 1 diabetes or on insulin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 350.6 Td (- Severely underweight individuals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 336.6 Td (- People with certain medical conditions \(ask your doctor\)) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
